race.comment: MR BUSTER (1) was switched north by the Ciaron Maher stable and was narrowly beaten at Doomben over a mile. Proven second-up and the step up in distance will advantage. He has more to give and the in-form Maloney retains the ride. ROCK THE SUNRISE (3) was nudged out here over 1400m and then came back 3 weeks later and was beaten 2.4L over a mile in stronger than this. Maps for the run of the race and the 1800m is sure to suit. A player. LARIDAE (2) was heavily bet delivering an easy 58 win at the Gold Coast over this journey. He keeps improving and the 3kg claim brings him into it. THROTTLE RESPONSE (8) is a lightly raced galloper from the Waller yard showing promise. Missed a whisker in a CL1 over the 1800m second-up and he will also be around the mark.
